					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Agastyēśvara shrine at the foot of the hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarmaṉ Rājarājaṉ-Sundara-pāṇḍyadēva.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is built in at the end and damaged.</p>						

						<p>It gives details of date such as <hi rend="italic">trayōdaśi,</hi> Monday and Puṉarpūśa, the other details being in the built-in part. </p>						

						<p>It seems to register the sale of the village Muḷḷikkuṇḍu, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa</hi> of god Tēṉāṟṟu-Nāyakar, as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā-kāṇi</hi> to a person (name lost), by the trustees of the temple of the god mentioned above.</p>						

						</summary>
